Class CommonUser

  • java.lang.Object
    • django.contrib.auth.models.User
      • CommonUser

  • public class CommonUser
extends django.contrib.auth.models.User
    The common (non-developer) user. This user can subscribe to lists and has a SubscriptionSettings object for each list it is subscribed to. By using the django User base-class, we can have assured security with regards to user authentication.

        public IOSDevice register_device(java.lang.String device_token,
                                 boolean commit)
        Adds a device denoted by the given device token to this user's list of owned devices.
        Parameters:
        device_token - the device token (32 characters) given by APNS
        commit - if true, returned device is saved. if false, it's not saved and only returned.
        Returns:
        the created device
